WEBVTT

00:01.736 --> 00:02.735
How long has your sister
lived with you?

00:02.737 --> 00:03.736
Sorry if she seemed rude.

00:03.738 --> 00:05.404
She seemed high.

00:05.406 --> 00:07.340
You know, at first, you're
pissed, and then you accept it.

00:07.342 --> 00:09.675
Then you're just
the caregiver.
She's my sister.

00:09.677 --> 00:11.544
And I'll help her through it.

00:11.546 --> 00:13.212
[ Sniffs ]
Give me some.

00:13.214 --> 00:15.014
[ Sniffs ]

00:15.016 --> 00:17.016
Start the car!
Start the car!

00:17.018 --> 00:20.219
Let's go!
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

00:20.221 --> 00:23.222
Smurf: Have you noticed anything
different about Julia and Baz?

00:23.224 --> 00:25.758
-Like what?
-They seem closer.

00:25.760 --> 00:27.426
Julia:
Andrew, I'm sorry!

00:27.428 --> 00:29.562
[ Retching ]
No!
Andrew, wait!

00:29.564 --> 00:30.629
Stop!

00:30.631 --> 00:31.830
[ Grunting ]

00:31.832 --> 00:32.965
Pope: Who is she?!

00:32.967 --> 00:34.700
Taylor: She's a cop!
She's a cop!

00:34.702 --> 00:36.569
You call her.

00:36.571 --> 00:37.570
You tell her
you wanna meet.

00:37.572 --> 00:39.638
Who killed
Catherine Belen?

00:39.640 --> 00:40.839
You?

00:40.841 --> 00:43.108
You wanna kill me, Andrew?
Go ahead.

00:43.110 --> 00:45.244
They can only
fry you once.

00:45.246 --> 00:46.579
She's your sister.

00:46.581 --> 00:47.980
No, Smurf.
She's not.

00:47.982 --> 00:50.649
In this house,
we're all family.
Then I'll leave.

00:50.651 --> 00:52.918
You know you're too old
for the orphanage, right?

00:52.920 --> 00:53.986
Pope: She knows.

00:53.988 --> 00:54.987
She knows what?

00:54.989 --> 00:57.456
I killed Cath.

00:57.458 --> 00:59.325
I did it for Smurf.

01:00.527 --> 01:04.063
♪♪

01:04.065 --> 01:10.002
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:10.004 --> 01:13.939
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:13.941 --> 01:17.076
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:19.947 --> 01:25.618
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:25.620 --> 01:29.021
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:29.023 --> 01:32.325
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:36.030 --> 01:38.897
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:38.899 --> 01:42.768
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:42.770 --> 01:46.639
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:46.641 --> 01:50.375
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:50.377 --> 01:54.513
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:54.515 --> 01:58.517
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

01:58.519 --> 02:00.419
♪ Got a ♪

02:15.936 --> 02:17.803
[ Engine shuts off ]

02:18.205 --> 02:20.939
[ Renn sighs ]

02:20.941 --> 02:23.676
Hey.
Thanks for coming.

02:23.678 --> 02:26.745
You score?

02:26.747 --> 02:28.481
No.

02:29.684 --> 02:34.086
♪♪

02:34.088 --> 02:35.888
Is he okay?

02:35.890 --> 02:37.690
Yeah.
I gave him some formula.

02:37.692 --> 02:40.025
Hi.

02:40.027 --> 02:41.560
<i> Hola, mi amor.</i>

02:41.562 --> 02:45.030
♪♪

02:45.032 --> 02:46.565
Let's go.

02:46.567 --> 02:48.301
[ Engine starts ]

02:48.303 --> 02:55.708
♪♪

02:55.710 --> 02:58.311
Is Pope up yet?

02:58.313 --> 03:00.579
No. I tried calling Craig.
I got nothing.

03:00.581 --> 03:02.247
Alright, well,
we should go talk to him.

03:02.249 --> 03:03.582
Do you wanna wake him up?

03:03.584 --> 03:05.250
We need to know what the hell
is going on, man.

03:05.252 --> 03:06.919
They could have cops
coming over here right now.

03:06.921 --> 03:08.821
Yeah, alright. Fine.

03:17.398 --> 03:20.132
His phone and wallet
are here.

03:20.134 --> 03:21.667
You see him leave?
No.

03:21.669 --> 03:23.336
Pope!

03:23.338 --> 03:31.344
♪♪

03:31.346 --> 03:39.218
♪♪

03:39.220 --> 03:41.820
Maybe he went to the skate park?
I'll drive over there.

03:41.822 --> 03:43.488
Find Craig.

03:43.490 --> 03:46.692
♪♪

03:46.694 --> 03:51.030
[ Engines starting ]

03:51.032 --> 03:57.636
♪♪

03:57.638 --> 04:03.576
♪♪

04:03.578 --> 04:05.978
Louise: Thanks for coming,
Detective.

04:05.980 --> 04:09.314
I need you to put me in touch
with your partner, Patrick.

04:09.316 --> 04:11.384
I left messages.
Ex-partner.

04:11.386 --> 04:16.255
He moved to Denver
to be closer to his grandkids.

04:16.257 --> 04:18.591
He ever spoke about
Catherine Belen?

04:18.593 --> 04:20.793
Yeah. Too much.

04:20.795 --> 04:23.596
From what I hear,
sounds like maybe you do, too.

04:25.332 --> 04:26.999
Her killer is still
walking around.

04:27.001 --> 04:29.001
Her killer's dead.

04:29.003 --> 04:31.737
It wasn't
Baz Blackwell.

04:31.739 --> 04:34.139
It was Pope Cody.

04:34.141 --> 04:37.476
I need you to pick him up
and bring him to the station.

04:37.478 --> 04:39.544
He has an unregistered firearm
in his car.

04:39.546 --> 04:41.680
That he used to kill
Catherine Belen?

04:41.682 --> 04:44.650
No. I need him in custody
so I can talk to him.

04:48.089 --> 04:50.222
I'm gonna need
something real.

04:50.224 --> 04:51.891
No fishing.

04:51.893 --> 04:57.029
♪♪

04:57.031 --> 05:02.501
♪♪

05:02.503 --> 05:04.903
Pancakes?

05:04.905 --> 05:06.105
Hey.

05:06.107 --> 05:12.645
♪♪

05:12.647 --> 05:19.251
♪♪

05:19.253 --> 05:21.253
Blockbuster got
the "Halloweens" back in.

05:21.255 --> 05:24.056
We could do
a movie marathon today.

05:24.058 --> 05:25.991
It's such a beautiful day
outside.

05:25.993 --> 05:28.494
You don't want to sit
in front of the TV all day.

05:33.000 --> 05:35.734
Oh.

05:35.736 --> 05:37.937
Welcome home, baby.

05:39.941 --> 05:42.041
Did you have a good night?

05:47.614 --> 05:50.449
Actually, I need you to watch
the boys for me today.

05:52.687 --> 05:53.886
Why?

05:53.888 --> 05:56.289
Baz and I have
errands to run.

05:56.291 --> 05:58.057
They'll be fine
on their own.

06:03.364 --> 06:05.164
Andrew...

06:05.166 --> 06:08.633
I can take that, baby.
Thank you.

06:08.635 --> 06:10.236
I'm sorry.

06:12.707 --> 06:14.840
[ Dishes clatter ]

06:14.842 --> 06:23.048
♪♪

06:23.050 --> 06:31.256
♪♪

06:31.258 --> 06:34.459
[ Cellphone rings ]

06:34.461 --> 06:35.660
Hey.

06:35.662 --> 06:37.930
Where are you?

06:37.932 --> 06:40.199
<i> What's going on?</i>

06:40.201 --> 06:42.335
Cindy OD'd.

06:42.337 --> 06:44.136
I'm at the hospital.

06:44.138 --> 06:45.938
They gave her a shot
of something,

06:45.940 --> 06:48.541
<i> but it was close.</i>

06:48.543 --> 06:49.742
Jesus.

06:49.744 --> 06:51.410
<i> I found her</i>
<i> on the bathroom floor.</i>

06:51.412 --> 06:53.412
<i> I thought she was dead.</i>

06:53.414 --> 06:56.549
Can you --
Can you come to the hospital?

06:56.551 --> 06:57.750
Um...

06:57.752 --> 06:59.018
uh, I can't right now.

06:59.020 --> 07:01.887
J...

07:01.889 --> 07:03.088
I need you.

07:03.090 --> 07:04.357
Yeah, I'm sorry.

07:04.359 --> 07:06.825
Now's not a good time,
Penny.

07:06.827 --> 07:08.093
Yeah. Mm-hmm.

07:08.095 --> 07:09.294
Okay. Sure.

07:09.296 --> 07:11.597
Whatever. I gotta go.
[ Sniffles ]

07:12.499 --> 07:14.700
[ Sighing ]
God damn it.

07:14.702 --> 07:22.507
♪♪

07:22.509 --> 07:30.249
♪♪

07:30.251 --> 07:32.084
Craig?

07:36.191 --> 07:38.123
Craig.

07:38.125 --> 07:44.663
♪♪

07:44.665 --> 07:46.131
Pope.

07:46.133 --> 07:51.804
♪♪

07:51.806 --> 07:57.342
♪♪

07:57.344 --> 07:59.145
What are you
doing here?

08:02.083 --> 08:04.683
This is where
I killed her.

08:04.685 --> 08:06.652
♪♪

08:10.792 --> 08:12.191
[ Door tones chime ]

08:12.193 --> 08:14.694
Alright.
Uh, here you go.

08:16.264 --> 08:18.130
I have to get
out of here.

08:18.132 --> 08:19.264
Alright, just...

08:19.266 --> 08:22.401
give me
a second, okay?

08:22.403 --> 08:25.805
I mean Oceanside.

08:25.807 --> 08:28.207
I can't keep doing this.

08:28.209 --> 08:30.876
Doing what?

08:30.878 --> 08:33.412
Nick got kidnapped two days ago,
and what do I do?

08:33.414 --> 08:35.881
Get high for two days.

08:35.883 --> 08:38.684
Renn, we both did.

08:40.154 --> 08:43.422
And Nick's fine.
Aren't you, bud?

08:43.424 --> 08:45.691
I should've quit dealing
when he was born, like you said.

08:45.693 --> 08:46.758
Sorry.

08:46.760 --> 08:49.462
Stop dealing,
and we'll be fine.

08:51.965 --> 08:53.633
But what's that got to do
with leaving Oceanside?

08:53.635 --> 08:55.301
I can't do it
in Oceanside.

08:55.303 --> 08:57.737
It's too easy
to get sucked back in.

08:59.907 --> 09:01.841
I have my<i> tías</i>
in San Antonio.

09:01.843 --> 09:03.375
The ones in Texas?

09:03.377 --> 09:06.846
I spent summers there
as a kid, remember?

09:06.848 --> 09:09.981
It's the only place I ever felt
like life was...

09:09.983 --> 09:10.983
normal.

09:10.985 --> 09:14.353
Renn, you're not taking
Nick to Texas.

09:18.726 --> 09:20.526
Come with us.

09:22.730 --> 09:25.797
You want to be with us, right?
With me?

09:25.799 --> 09:28.534
Look, Renn, this is our home.
Alright?

09:28.536 --> 09:32.804
We'll figure it out,
and we'll get through this.

09:32.806 --> 09:38.210
♪♪

09:38.212 --> 09:39.879
J: Hey.
Hey.

09:39.881 --> 09:42.281
What's up?

09:42.283 --> 09:44.149
You wanna go lay down?

09:44.151 --> 09:45.751
Alright?

09:51.893 --> 09:53.225
Where was he?

09:53.227 --> 09:55.427
At Craig's.

09:55.429 --> 09:57.229
He said that's
where it happened.

09:57.231 --> 09:59.231
Catherine?

09:59.233 --> 10:00.632
In Baz's bed.

10:00.634 --> 10:01.701
Jesus.

10:01.703 --> 10:03.369
Okay, well, he needs
a lawyer then.

10:03.371 --> 10:04.836
No. We need to get him
out of the country.

10:04.838 --> 10:06.506
We need to take him to Mexico,
get on a plane --
No, no.

10:06.508 --> 10:07.839
It's too late
for that, man.

10:07.841 --> 10:09.108
He hasn't been charged
with anything yet.

10:09.110 --> 10:10.509
Yeah, but if he runs,

10:10.511 --> 10:11.843
they'll be all over us
looking for him, man.

10:11.845 --> 10:13.379
Look, I don't think this cop
has shit on him, okay?

10:13.381 --> 10:15.381
If she did, h-he would
have been arrested already.

10:15.383 --> 10:16.849
Trust me.

10:22.590 --> 10:24.456
Let's get a lawyer.

10:24.458 --> 10:26.392
I'll talk to Pope.

10:26.394 --> 10:28.327
Okay, I'll make some calls
in the car,

10:28.329 --> 10:29.795
try and find
a good criminal attorney.

10:29.797 --> 10:31.530
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Where are you going?

10:31.532 --> 10:33.999
I've, uh, got to go deal
with something.

10:34.001 --> 10:35.401
Right now?

10:35.403 --> 10:37.737
Yeah, I gotta help a friend.
It won't take long.

10:37.739 --> 10:40.272
Just -- Just talk to him,
alright?

10:40.274 --> 10:44.009
See what else you can get
out of him about this cop.

10:44.011 --> 10:47.413
He listens to you, man.
He -- He trusts you.

10:47.415 --> 10:49.081
He doesn't listen to me.

10:49.083 --> 10:56.355
♪♪

10:56.357 --> 11:03.895
♪♪

11:03.897 --> 11:05.865
You can't ignore me
forever.

11:07.769 --> 11:10.670
Andrew, come on.
I don't want
to talk about it.

11:12.640 --> 11:14.706
We were gonna
tell you --
When?

11:14.708 --> 11:17.910
We were.
I swear.

11:17.912 --> 11:19.378
He's our brother.

11:19.380 --> 11:21.380
He's not our brother.

11:21.382 --> 11:26.118
♪♪

11:26.120 --> 11:28.120
It's just...

11:28.122 --> 11:29.922
not right.

11:29.924 --> 11:31.923
It's disgusting.

11:31.925 --> 11:39.064
♪♪

11:39.066 --> 11:42.568
So, are you mad at Baz,
too, or just me?

11:46.140 --> 11:47.807
Fine.

11:47.809 --> 11:54.279
♪♪

11:54.281 --> 12:00.486
♪♪

12:00.488 --> 12:05.625
♪ I can let you in,
let you settle in ♪

12:05.627 --> 12:10.630
♪ I can take it off,
show you what you want ♪

12:10.632 --> 12:15.635
♪ In another place,
there's another face ♪

12:15.637 --> 12:20.972
♪ I can take it off,
show you what you want ♪

12:20.974 --> 12:25.977
♪ In another place,
in another place ♪

12:25.979 --> 12:31.651
♪ In another place,
in another ♪

12:31.653 --> 12:35.587
[ Labored breathing ]

12:35.589 --> 12:36.788
[ Grunts ]

12:36.790 --> 12:38.590
[ Telephone ringing ]

12:38.592 --> 12:43.729
♪ There's a resonance,
that's been making sense ♪

12:43.731 --> 12:48.534
♪ I can turn it off,
show you what you want ♪

12:48.536 --> 12:53.739
♪ In another place,
there's another face ♪
[ Ringing continues ]

12:53.741 --> 12:58.477
♪ I can take it off,
show you what you want ♪

12:58.479 --> 13:03.683
♪ In another place,
in another place ♪
[ Exhales sharply, grunts ]

13:03.685 --> 13:07.019
♪ In another place,
in another ♪

13:07.021 --> 13:10.556
Brittany:
You're here early.

13:10.558 --> 13:12.824
So, you just gonna
let it ring?

13:12.826 --> 13:14.159
Isn't that your job?

13:14.161 --> 13:17.629
[ Ringing continues ]

13:17.631 --> 13:20.366
[ Weights clank ]

13:20.368 --> 13:22.502
Hello, Workya--
Yeah.

13:24.305 --> 13:26.906
Yeah, okay.
Hold on.

13:28.976 --> 13:30.976
It's your brother.

13:30.978 --> 13:32.177
Yeah?

13:32.179 --> 13:35.915
♪ To another place,
to another place ♪

13:35.917 --> 13:38.650
Just tell him
I'll call him back.

13:38.652 --> 13:40.853
He says he'll call you --
Yeah.

13:42.256 --> 13:44.056
Okay.

13:44.058 --> 13:46.526
He says to get your ass
down to the house now.

13:46.528 --> 13:47.927
Something about Pope.

13:47.929 --> 13:49.461
[ Grunting ]

13:49.463 --> 13:50.862
[ Weights clank ]

13:50.864 --> 13:54.734
♪♪

13:54.736 --> 13:58.270
[ Coin clattering,
keypad beeping ]

13:58.272 --> 14:00.406
[ Machine whirs ]

14:05.947 --> 14:07.413
Hi.

14:07.415 --> 14:09.415
You're here.

14:09.417 --> 14:11.817
I-I can't stay long.

14:11.819 --> 14:14.886
But, um...
how is she?

14:14.888 --> 14:17.489
They shocked her
back into breathing.

14:17.491 --> 14:19.158
My mom flatlined
a few times.

14:19.160 --> 14:21.093
Once for over
two minutes.

14:23.030 --> 14:26.365
Your mom died,
though, right?

14:26.367 --> 14:27.967
Yeah.

14:30.171 --> 14:31.938
I'm sorry.

14:40.248 --> 14:43.582
Noah's coming home.

14:43.584 --> 14:45.918
Oh, yeah?
For how long?

14:45.920 --> 14:49.121
He's redeployed to Pendleton,
so at least a year.

14:49.123 --> 14:52.992
Unless someone else
starts a new war.

14:52.994 --> 14:55.527
He's already said that he wants
to kick my sister out

14:55.529 --> 14:56.862
when he gets back.

14:56.864 --> 14:58.998
I don't -- I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

14:59.000 --> 15:02.134
I'm gonna be fighting with her
or for her

15:02.136 --> 15:03.936
for the rest
of my life.

15:03.938 --> 15:05.605
You shouldn't have to.

15:05.607 --> 15:08.740
So, what, Noah's right?
I should just throw her out?

15:08.742 --> 15:11.210
Is that what you did?

15:11.212 --> 15:13.479
Cindy's not your kid.

15:13.481 --> 15:15.280
You're not her mom.

15:15.282 --> 15:19.084
What I'm saying is that she's
not your responsibility anymore.

15:19.086 --> 15:21.220
But I get it.

15:21.222 --> 15:22.688
I do. Trust me.

15:22.690 --> 15:26.626
♪♪

15:26.628 --> 15:28.227
I gotta go.

15:28.229 --> 15:29.761
Already?
Yeah.

15:29.763 --> 15:33.765
I've got family shit
of my own to deal with.

15:33.767 --> 15:36.836
Are you okay?

15:36.838 --> 15:38.971
No.

15:38.973 --> 15:40.973
Did they say
when she's getting out?

15:40.975 --> 15:43.375
Not for a while.
Okay.

15:43.377 --> 15:45.711
I'll try to
come back later.
Okay.

15:45.713 --> 15:47.647
Thanks for coming.
Of course.

15:47.649 --> 15:54.386
♪♪

15:54.388 --> 15:56.322
[ Knocking ]

15:56.324 --> 15:59.225
♪♪

16:03.998 --> 16:06.132
Deran: I, uh,
made you a sandwich.

16:08.202 --> 16:10.002
We need to talk.

16:26.487 --> 16:28.788
Do you know what
this cop has on you?

16:32.159 --> 16:35.961
No.
I don't know shit.

16:35.963 --> 16:39.098
What do you know
about her?

16:39.100 --> 16:41.166
She's not
from Oceanside.

16:41.168 --> 16:43.703
Okay.
Where is she from?

16:43.705 --> 16:46.505
I don't know.

16:46.507 --> 16:48.440
State, maybe county.

16:48.442 --> 16:50.309
So, some cop who's not
from Oceanside

16:50.311 --> 16:53.445
just shows up and starts
asking questions about Cath.

16:53.447 --> 16:55.314
Not asking, man.

16:55.316 --> 16:58.250
[ Inhales deeply ]

16:58.252 --> 16:59.785
Sh-She knows.

16:59.787 --> 17:01.587
She knows what?

17:01.589 --> 17:03.522
She knows what I did.

17:03.524 --> 17:05.657
How could she
know that?

17:05.659 --> 17:07.360
I don't know.

17:11.665 --> 17:13.633
[ Sighs ]

17:15.136 --> 17:21.673
♪♪

17:21.675 --> 17:28.214
♪♪

17:28.216 --> 17:31.751
I gotta get you
food now, too?

17:31.753 --> 17:33.219
Oh, it's the least thing
you could do

17:33.221 --> 17:36.021
after you almost
got me killed.

17:36.023 --> 17:37.823
Pope Cody came
to my motel.

17:37.825 --> 17:40.492
Why would he do that?

17:40.494 --> 17:41.827
I have no idea.

17:41.829 --> 17:44.896
Maybe you told him
there was heat on him.
No, I didn't.

17:44.898 --> 17:46.966
[ Fence clangs ]

17:46.968 --> 17:48.634
After he came
to<i> my</i> motel,

17:48.636 --> 17:50.169
you don't think he's gonna
come for you next?

17:50.171 --> 17:52.905
No, he already
kicked my ass.

17:52.907 --> 17:55.174
Really? When?

17:55.176 --> 17:57.643
You need to tell me
everything that happened.

17:57.645 --> 17:59.712
♪♪

18:06.186 --> 18:09.722
Smurf: Look around.
I want your opinion.

18:09.724 --> 18:11.523
Yeah, it's fine.

18:11.525 --> 18:13.259
It's just fine?

18:14.262 --> 18:15.862
[ Scoffs ]

18:15.864 --> 18:17.529
What, you bought this?

18:17.531 --> 18:18.731
Yeah.

18:18.733 --> 18:20.132
Out of foreclosure.

18:20.134 --> 18:22.668
The owner was going bankrupt,
so I got it for a steal.

18:22.670 --> 18:25.137
And what are you
gonna do with it?

18:25.139 --> 18:28.807
I was thinking
of renting it.

18:28.809 --> 18:31.209
What do you think?
About what?

18:31.211 --> 18:33.011
Renting it?
[ Laughs ]

18:33.013 --> 18:35.881
I figure,
if we get this place

18:35.883 --> 18:38.751
and we have the house
on Whaley,

18:38.753 --> 18:40.753
that we could
have ourselves a little

18:40.755 --> 18:42.755
property management
business.

18:44.492 --> 18:47.159
You could collect checks.

18:47.161 --> 18:48.895
You could fix
the toilets.

18:48.897 --> 18:53.966
You could, you know,
clean up the cat piss.

18:53.968 --> 18:56.235
Is that what you want?
No.

18:58.372 --> 19:00.439
Really? Hm.

19:00.441 --> 19:02.641
I just assumed, 'cause of
the way you've been acting.

19:02.643 --> 19:04.110
What's that
supposed to mean?

19:04.112 --> 19:08.847
If you want a low-rent life
where you surf, get high,

19:08.849 --> 19:11.684
marry the local girl
with teased hair...

19:13.588 --> 19:15.521
I can give you that.

19:15.523 --> 19:17.856
Yeah.
I don't want that.

19:17.858 --> 19:21.393
'Cause you and I both know
what it's like to have nothing,

19:21.395 --> 19:23.195
but I think
I spoiled you.

19:23.197 --> 19:26.999
I let you
get comfortable.

19:27.001 --> 19:29.401
I let you forget

19:29.403 --> 19:33.005
that this life
doesn't come for free.

19:33.007 --> 19:34.606
Yeah,
I know it doesn't.

19:34.608 --> 19:36.342
No, you don't.

19:36.344 --> 19:39.611
If you did, you wouldn't be
getting sloppy.

19:39.613 --> 19:44.951
♪♪

19:44.953 --> 19:46.819
This place is yours,

19:46.821 --> 19:49.688
but the bullshit...

19:49.690 --> 19:53.025
stops here.

19:53.027 --> 19:54.861
Really?

19:55.763 --> 19:57.029
[ Laughs ]

19:57.031 --> 19:58.764
Hey.

20:00.969 --> 20:04.637
No more teenage drama,
okay?

20:04.639 --> 20:06.739
Yeah.
No, really.

20:10.044 --> 20:12.378
You keep your focus.

20:14.649 --> 20:16.515
Okay.

20:16.517 --> 20:23.389
♪♪

20:23.391 --> 20:24.790
J: I found a lawyer.

20:24.792 --> 20:28.060
He's 800 bucks an hour, but he
used to be a federal prosecutor

20:28.062 --> 20:29.328
and he's got a great
acquittal record

20:29.330 --> 20:30.997
for the rest
of his clients.

20:30.999 --> 20:32.999
If we knew this cop's name,
we could find out

20:33.001 --> 20:36.335
some more information
on our own.

20:36.337 --> 20:40.138
All Pope said is that
she's not from Oceanside, so...

20:40.140 --> 20:41.807
'Sup?
Hey.

20:41.809 --> 20:43.342
What's going on?

20:43.344 --> 20:44.610
You alright?

20:44.612 --> 20:48.547
Yeah, it's just me and Renn
got into it last night.

20:48.549 --> 20:49.548
What's up?

20:49.550 --> 20:51.483
There's a cop
looking at Pope.

20:51.485 --> 20:53.219
For what?

20:53.221 --> 20:55.621
For killing Cath.

20:55.623 --> 20:57.289
Wait.
Uh, Baz's Cath?

20:57.291 --> 20:58.624
Mm-hmm.

20:58.626 --> 21:00.426
But she ran off.

21:00.428 --> 21:02.561
No, she's dead.

21:02.563 --> 21:04.496
Well, why do they think
it's Pope?

21:04.498 --> 21:06.965
Because it was.

21:06.967 --> 21:08.166
What? Why?

21:08.168 --> 21:10.168
He told us last night.

21:10.170 --> 21:11.570
The hell are you
talking about, man?

21:11.572 --> 21:13.572
Where is he?
He's not saying shit.

21:13.574 --> 21:15.274
He's in his room.

21:18.446 --> 21:20.312
Pope.

21:20.314 --> 21:22.248
Get your ass up.

21:22.250 --> 21:24.383
How 'bout you get up
and tell me what's going on?

21:24.385 --> 21:26.052
Go away.
Get up.

21:26.054 --> 21:29.521
[ Grunting ] Get up.

21:29.523 --> 21:32.124
Get up!

21:34.262 --> 21:35.461
Quit it!

21:35.463 --> 21:38.464
Let's go.

21:38.466 --> 21:44.403
♪♪

21:44.405 --> 21:45.604
Aah!

21:45.606 --> 21:47.540
[ Breathing heavily ]

21:47.542 --> 21:53.546
♪♪

21:53.548 --> 21:55.548
Hey. Hey, look.

21:55.550 --> 21:57.549
Look at me.
Look -- Look at me.

21:57.551 --> 22:00.152
We need to talk,
alright?

22:00.154 --> 22:01.620
Yeah?
We're got to talk.

22:01.622 --> 22:03.155
Alright, so you're gonna
get dressed

22:03.157 --> 22:05.157
and you're gonna meet me
in the living room.

22:05.159 --> 22:07.626
You got it?
Yeah. Yeah.

22:07.628 --> 22:08.827
Okay.

22:08.829 --> 22:13.832
♪♪

22:13.834 --> 22:15.367
[ Groans ]

22:15.369 --> 22:21.908
♪♪

22:21.910 --> 22:23.909
Julia:
Are you packing?

22:23.911 --> 22:27.313
Yeah, Smurf got me
a place.

22:27.315 --> 22:29.715
What?
Yeah, on the Strand.

22:29.717 --> 22:31.984
She bought you a house?
No.

22:31.986 --> 22:35.854
[ Chuckles ]
No, but I can stay there.

22:35.856 --> 22:37.856
You said yes?

22:37.858 --> 22:40.793
Yeah, why wouldn't I?

22:40.795 --> 22:43.529
Baz, you know what it means
to accept shit from her.

22:43.531 --> 22:46.265
Yeah, like you turned down
your new car, right?

22:48.402 --> 22:51.737
Hey, there's nothing wrong
with playing along.

22:51.739 --> 22:53.573
The perks are nice.

22:56.410 --> 22:57.443
Hey.

23:01.615 --> 23:04.883
This way, we don't have
to sneak around.

23:04.885 --> 23:07.620
No Andrew,
no any of that bullshit.

23:07.622 --> 23:09.621
But you're just leaving?

23:09.623 --> 23:12.959
No, you can come over
whenever.

23:12.961 --> 23:15.094
Hey, you'll see.

23:18.699 --> 23:20.899
She's not done.

23:20.901 --> 23:24.637
She's never done until she gets
things the way she wants them.

23:24.639 --> 23:32.444
♪♪

23:32.446 --> 23:33.712
Hey.

23:33.714 --> 23:37.850
Make yourselves at home here,
and are you hungry?

23:37.852 --> 23:39.117
Yeah.

23:39.119 --> 23:40.987
Yeah, I was thinking
of making some lunch.

23:40.989 --> 23:42.921
-Sounds good, yeah.
-Nice.

23:43.123 --> 23:44.857
-[ Laughing ]
-Awesome.

23:44.859 --> 23:47.259
Julia:
Who the hell are they?

23:47.261 --> 23:50.596
Just some friends
I met on the beach.

23:50.598 --> 23:55.067
Would you go and get
your brother for me?

23:55.069 --> 23:56.736
Fine.

24:02.210 --> 24:04.076
<i> Hadouken!</i>

24:06.014 --> 24:08.947
Ah.
There you are.

24:08.949 --> 24:10.816
Hey, Andrew.

24:10.818 --> 24:13.686
<i> Hadouken!</i>

24:13.688 --> 24:15.954
Pope?

24:15.956 --> 24:17.489
Could you come outside?

24:17.491 --> 24:20.226
I have some friends
I want to introduce you to.

24:20.228 --> 24:21.760
<i> Shoryuken!</i>

24:21.762 --> 24:23.629
Who?
Just come on.

24:23.631 --> 24:25.364
<i> Hadouken!</i>

24:25.900 --> 24:27.133
[ Sighs ]

24:30.104 --> 24:35.173
This is Mandy, Kendra,
and Alison.

24:35.175 --> 24:37.710
-Hi.
-Come sit with us.

24:37.712 --> 24:39.378
Introduce yourself.

24:39.380 --> 24:41.047
Don't be rude.

24:41.049 --> 24:45.317
♪♪

24:45.319 --> 24:47.185
What's your name?

24:47.187 --> 24:49.255
Um, Pope.

24:49.257 --> 24:51.057
Julia:
I know what you're doing.

24:51.059 --> 24:52.591
What are you
afraid of?

24:52.593 --> 24:55.994
He's gonna like one of them
better than he likes you?

24:55.996 --> 25:00.933
♪♪

25:00.935 --> 25:02.935
Smurf said
she was a CI.

25:02.937 --> 25:04.704
And was she?

25:07.141 --> 25:09.141
No, I don't think she was.

25:11.345 --> 25:13.079
Craig: Where'd you do it?
Why does that matter?

25:13.081 --> 25:15.481
For evidence.
It's been years.

25:15.483 --> 25:17.950
Well, blood can stay
in floorboards for a long time.

25:17.952 --> 25:19.151
There was no blood.

25:19.153 --> 25:20.720
Where did you
do it, Pope?

25:22.957 --> 25:24.022
Baz's house.

25:24.024 --> 25:25.691
In my place?

25:25.693 --> 25:26.759
J: Yeah.

25:26.761 --> 25:27.960
Craig: Jesus.

25:27.962 --> 25:29.628
Deran:
In the bedroom.

25:29.630 --> 25:31.163
Smurf made him do it.

25:31.165 --> 25:34.700
But you could've said no.
Couldn't you?

25:34.702 --> 25:38.171
When did any of us
ever say no to Smurf?

25:39.774 --> 25:40.973
Hmm?

25:40.975 --> 25:50.316
♪♪

25:50.318 --> 25:52.118
[ Glass shatters ]

25:52.120 --> 25:55.488
♪♪

25:59.860 --> 26:01.394
Deran: What can you tell us
about this cop?

26:01.396 --> 26:03.062
Her name's Louise Thompson,
and you're right --

26:03.064 --> 26:04.397
she's not from
Oceanside.

26:04.399 --> 26:06.399
So, what's she
doing here?

26:06.401 --> 26:08.934
They found Catherine Belen's
body in Riverside.

26:08.936 --> 26:10.269
She works cold cases there,

26:10.271 --> 26:12.537
so she must be here
to look into Andrew.

26:12.539 --> 26:14.607
So, she's not even homicide?
Not anymore.

26:14.609 --> 26:16.942
She got a CI killed
working a case last year.

26:16.944 --> 26:17.810
Jesus.

26:17.812 --> 26:19.544
If she crosses a line
with Andrew,

26:19.546 --> 26:20.879
we can establish
a pattern.

26:20.881 --> 26:22.547
Well, she already
has crossed a line.

26:22.549 --> 26:24.216
I mean, she's been
tailing him.

26:24.218 --> 26:25.418
Really?

26:25.420 --> 26:28.754
She, uh --
She broke into the house.

26:28.756 --> 26:30.555
What do you mean
she broke into the house?

26:30.557 --> 26:32.357
-How'd she get into the house?
-Did she take anything?

26:32.359 --> 26:33.692
I don't think
she took anything.

26:33.694 --> 26:35.227
David: Well, we can use
all of this.

26:35.229 --> 26:36.695
If she was in here
without a warrant,

26:36.697 --> 26:39.899
we can get any possible case
thrown out on that alone.

26:39.901 --> 26:41.700
Unfortunately,

26:41.702 --> 26:44.369
that's not the only charge that
Andrew's facing right now.

26:44.371 --> 26:45.905
Okay.
What's the other charge?

26:45.907 --> 26:48.774
I discovered that Oceanside PD
is gonna be issuing a warrant

26:48.776 --> 26:50.576
for Andrew's arrest
for assault.

26:50.578 --> 26:53.312
The victim is someone
named Taylor Cline.

26:53.314 --> 26:55.314
Does that sound
familiar?
Yes.

26:55.316 --> 26:56.649
The kid
from the skate park.

26:56.651 --> 26:58.183
She put him there,
the cop.

26:58.185 --> 27:00.119
Wait, what's that got to do
with an old murder case?

27:00.121 --> 27:02.121
She probably doesn't have enough
for a homicide charge,

27:02.123 --> 27:04.990
so she convinced someone
from Oceanside to prop this up.

27:04.992 --> 27:06.659
Now that we're aware
of her investigation,

27:06.661 --> 27:08.861
she probably assumes
that Andrew may run,

27:08.863 --> 27:11.196
so we'll need to go down
and get you processed.

27:11.198 --> 27:13.398
You should be able to get bail,
but the previous

27:13.400 --> 27:15.468
felony conviction
may complicate things.

27:15.470 --> 27:17.803
He's just gonna walk down there
and turn himself in?

27:17.805 --> 27:20.273
It'll look better for us if we
go to the station, cooperate.

27:20.275 --> 27:22.275
How much can you raise
for bail?

27:22.277 --> 27:24.076
Enough.

27:24.078 --> 27:25.744
Half a million?
A million?

27:25.746 --> 27:27.146
For an assault
charge?

27:27.148 --> 27:30.215
Convicted bank robber.

27:30.217 --> 27:31.817
We got it.

27:33.955 --> 27:35.288
We got it.

27:35.290 --> 27:37.890
Alright.
Well, we'll all go with him.

27:37.892 --> 27:39.424
Only one of you.

27:39.426 --> 27:43.228
All of you will make this
a much bigger story.

27:43.230 --> 27:45.097
Okay.
I'll go with him.

27:45.099 --> 27:53.306
♪♪

27:53.308 --> 27:55.508
[ Laughter ]

27:58.645 --> 28:01.246
You think you could pick me up?
You look strong.

28:01.248 --> 28:02.915
Ooh, we should
play chicken.

28:02.917 --> 28:04.783
Mandy, come on.

28:04.785 --> 28:05.918
Andrew: Chicken?

28:05.920 --> 28:07.786
Yeah,
you ever played?

28:07.788 --> 28:08.988
Um...

28:08.990 --> 28:10.923
[ Laughs ]

28:11.926 --> 28:14.193
What kind of name is Pope,
anyway?

28:14.195 --> 28:16.595
Pope?
I thought it was Pulp.

28:16.597 --> 28:21.066
Hey, baby, wanna come and help
me put some snacks together?

28:21.068 --> 28:26.205
♪♪

28:26.207 --> 28:27.740
Bye!

28:27.742 --> 28:32.277
♪♪

28:32.279 --> 28:33.679
What's wrong?

28:33.681 --> 28:36.349
Nothing.

28:36.351 --> 28:38.651
Which one of them
do you like best?

28:41.022 --> 28:42.822
What do you mean?

28:45.292 --> 28:47.426
Which one do you want?

28:47.428 --> 28:53.232
♪♪

28:53.234 --> 28:55.234
I don't know.

28:57.038 --> 28:59.972
Don't be afraid.

28:59.974 --> 29:01.174
I'm not.

29:01.176 --> 29:03.242
Okay.

29:03.244 --> 29:05.644
Well, go on, then,
baby.

29:05.646 --> 29:08.247
Take what you want.

29:08.249 --> 29:14.053
♪♪

29:14.055 --> 29:19.659
♪♪

29:25.600 --> 29:28.667
You ready to go?

29:28.669 --> 29:33.472
When was the last time
the pool cleaner came?

29:33.474 --> 29:35.408
I don't know.

29:35.410 --> 29:37.376
There's algae.

29:39.146 --> 29:41.881
You remember when Craig
took a shit in the pool

29:41.883 --> 29:44.817
'cause he was mad
at Smurf?

29:44.819 --> 29:46.886
Yeah.

29:46.888 --> 29:49.554
[ Laughing ] You wouldn't swim
in it for like six months,

29:49.556 --> 29:51.023
even after
they drained it.

29:51.025 --> 29:53.326
It was filthy, man.

29:56.431 --> 30:00.966
I don't know, I guess this
is kinda like that.

30:00.968 --> 30:02.435
You know?

30:02.437 --> 30:05.571
Shit in the pool.

30:05.573 --> 30:08.808
Just gotta deal with it
and pretend it never happened.

30:12.980 --> 30:14.747
It did happen.

30:18.986 --> 30:21.587
Hey.

30:21.589 --> 30:25.190
You did it for us.
You know that, right?

30:25.192 --> 30:26.859
To protect us.

30:26.861 --> 30:28.794
You always have.

30:30.131 --> 30:31.764
[ Sniffles ]

30:33.600 --> 30:40.739
Remember how Smurf used to
make all of those ribs for us?

30:40.741 --> 30:43.709
After a job, you know,
when we did good?

30:46.547 --> 30:49.548
Piles of ribs
and coleslaw.

30:49.550 --> 30:51.083
[ Chuckles ]

30:51.085 --> 30:55.688
Baz always had to be in charge
of the grill, you know?

30:55.690 --> 30:57.757
[ Inhales shakily ]

30:59.226 --> 31:01.894
[ Voice breaking ]
That was good, man.

31:01.896 --> 31:09.502
♪♪

31:09.504 --> 31:11.170
Come on.

31:11.172 --> 31:13.973
Let's get this shit
over with, yeah?

31:13.975 --> 31:21.514
♪♪

31:21.516 --> 31:23.648
[ Music playing faintly ]

31:23.650 --> 31:28.787
♪ Try to tell you the truth ♪

31:28.789 --> 31:32.591
♪ Oh, baby,
don't make me cry ♪

31:32.593 --> 31:34.527
♪♪

31:34.529 --> 31:40.465
♪ You should be picking me up ♪

31:40.467 --> 31:46.405
♪ Instead you're dragging
me down ♪

31:46.407 --> 31:51.810
♪ Now I'm missing you more ♪

31:51.812 --> 31:58.017
♪ 'Cause, baby,
you're not around ♪

31:58.019 --> 32:01.554
♪ Now that you're not around ♪

32:01.556 --> 32:03.689
Mm.
What?

32:03.691 --> 32:05.490
Uh...
What's wrong?

32:05.492 --> 32:07.159
I-I don't...

32:07.161 --> 32:09.562
know.

32:09.564 --> 32:11.430
It's okay.

32:11.432 --> 32:13.232
I'll show you.

32:13.234 --> 32:22.641
♪♪

32:22.643 --> 32:32.185
♪♪

32:32.187 --> 32:34.319
[ Breathing heavily ]

32:34.321 --> 32:44.129
♪♪

32:44.131 --> 32:46.599
David: I'll let them know
we're here.

32:48.269 --> 32:50.535
I'm here with Andrew Cody.

32:50.537 --> 32:52.939
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:55.210 --> 32:57.743
Don't worry about
these assholes.

32:57.745 --> 33:00.479
Mr. Cody.
I'm Detective Hutchins.

33:00.481 --> 33:02.615
You're under arrest
for assault.

33:02.617 --> 33:05.350
Put your hands
behind your head.

33:05.352 --> 33:08.421
[ Handcuffs rattle ]

33:08.423 --> 33:10.555
You have the right
to remain silent.

33:10.557 --> 33:12.024
Anything you say
can and will

33:12.026 --> 33:14.159
be used against you
in a court of law.

33:14.161 --> 33:15.560
You have the right
to an attorney.

33:15.562 --> 33:16.762
He's aware of that.

33:16.764 --> 33:17.830
David: She has to finish
the Miranda.

33:17.832 --> 33:19.564
She knows I'm watching
this entire

33:19.566 --> 33:20.833
waste of
the taxpayers' money.

33:20.835 --> 33:22.835
If you cannot afford
an attorney,

33:22.837 --> 33:25.704
one will be
provided for you.

33:25.706 --> 33:27.372
Do you understand?

33:27.374 --> 33:29.008
Yeah.

33:55.602 --> 33:57.203
[ Door closes ]

33:58.539 --> 34:00.540
[ Keys rattle ]

34:17.158 --> 34:19.225
[ Door closes ]

34:23.698 --> 34:29.234
♪♪

34:29.236 --> 34:31.270
[ Exhales slowly ]

34:34.509 --> 34:36.775
I want my lawyer.

34:36.777 --> 34:38.978
I know.

34:38.980 --> 34:40.646
But I suggest
you hear me out first

34:40.648 --> 34:42.781
before your attorney
comes in --
I'm not listening.

34:42.783 --> 34:45.718
...and there's things you
and I won't be able to control.

34:45.720 --> 34:47.920
Like what happens
to Lena.

34:49.991 --> 34:53.326
She's why I'm here,
you know?

34:53.328 --> 34:56.395
'Cause we talked.

34:56.397 --> 34:58.364
Such a beautiful girl.

35:00.668 --> 35:03.202
So fragile.

35:03.204 --> 35:06.339
But that's understandable
considering what happened.

35:08.275 --> 35:10.943
Yeah, Lena had
an interesting story

35:10.945 --> 35:13.212
about the last night
she saw her mom alive.

35:13.214 --> 35:16.081
She said she remembers
you driving

35:16.083 --> 35:19.252
in the middle of the night
through the desert.

35:21.356 --> 35:23.488
Yeah.

35:23.490 --> 35:25.424
Lena remembers that.

35:25.426 --> 35:34.033
♪♪

35:34.035 --> 35:37.370
This is how we found
her mother.

35:37.372 --> 35:40.373
Go on. Look.

35:40.375 --> 35:42.441
Look.

35:42.443 --> 35:46.345
That sheet you wrapped her in
didn't do much.

35:49.050 --> 35:52.851
Animals got to her
pretty fast.

35:52.853 --> 35:55.388
I'm not gonna show this
to Lena,

35:55.390 --> 35:59.425
but the DA will
once they get you on trial.

36:02.063 --> 36:04.930
Is that what you want,
Andrew?

36:04.932 --> 36:06.465
For Lena to see this?

36:06.467 --> 36:10.169
And for the whole world to know
that her uncle murdered her mom?

36:12.740 --> 36:16.208
That trial will
destroy her life.

36:16.210 --> 36:19.078
But you can save her
from that.

36:19.080 --> 36:22.114
All you have to do
is admit to what happened.

36:24.885 --> 36:27.753
Funny thing is,
I think you want to.

36:30.825 --> 36:34.227
That's why you told Amy,
right?

36:38.299 --> 36:39.932
Yeah.

36:43.304 --> 36:46.238
I followed her home
that night you two had dinner,

36:46.240 --> 36:49.308
because I wanted her to know
who you really were.

36:51.512 --> 36:53.246
But she already knew.

36:53.248 --> 36:56.315
You gave her all the details,
huh, Andrew?

36:56.317 --> 36:58.117
She didn't want
to tell me,

36:58.119 --> 36:59.852
but you made her
an accessory to a crime.

36:59.854 --> 37:01.287
What else
was she gonna do?

37:03.524 --> 37:07.126
I don't think that trial
is good for her, either.

37:07.128 --> 37:09.795
Or for her son.

37:09.797 --> 37:11.764
Or her sobriety.

37:14.269 --> 37:17.503
Keeping your secret
would be like punishing her.

37:26.614 --> 37:29.148
Amy wanted you
to have this.

37:29.150 --> 37:31.417
She still cares
about you.

37:33.288 --> 37:35.788
She knows you didn't
want to do it.

37:37.358 --> 37:40.960
She knows you don't want to keep
hurting the people you love.

37:44.299 --> 37:48.167
You know the path
to redemption.

37:49.971 --> 37:53.438
There's only one way.

37:53.440 --> 37:55.308
Confess.

38:05.519 --> 38:07.786
[ Footsteps approaching ]

38:07.788 --> 38:10.456
Smurf: How'd it go?

38:10.458 --> 38:12.258
It went.

38:12.260 --> 38:13.926
Thank you, Kendra.
Mm-hmm.

38:13.928 --> 38:15.328
Here you go.

38:16.064 --> 38:18.530
Thank you.
Have a good night.

38:18.532 --> 38:20.166
You, too.

38:23.872 --> 38:25.838
Really?

38:27.207 --> 38:29.275
[ Glass thuds ]

38:29.277 --> 38:31.744
What?
What was the deal?

38:31.746 --> 38:34.146
Double
if you screw him?

38:34.148 --> 38:37.215
I'm trying to fix
what you broke, baby.

38:37.217 --> 38:39.818
You got him
all worked up.

38:39.820 --> 38:41.287
What was I
supposed to do?

38:41.289 --> 38:43.422
That is not
what he needs.

38:43.424 --> 38:45.491
Okay.
What does he need, little girl?

38:45.493 --> 38:48.226
To be away from you
and your bullshit, Smurf.

38:48.228 --> 38:50.829
Oh.
Is that right?

38:50.831 --> 38:56.902
♪♪

38:56.904 --> 39:00.839
You know, you should buy him
a house, too.

39:00.841 --> 39:03.910
What?

39:03.912 --> 39:07.113
This isn't about Andrew.

39:07.115 --> 39:09.315
This is about Baz.

39:09.317 --> 39:11.083
Again.

39:13.921 --> 39:16.789
You know...

39:16.791 --> 39:20.258
he might still be here

39:20.260 --> 39:23.329
if you two
hadn't been so reckless.

39:23.331 --> 39:29.468
♪♪

39:29.470 --> 39:35.207
♪♪

39:35.209 --> 39:37.075
[ Indistinct conversations ]

39:37.077 --> 39:39.878
Louise: Deran Cody.

39:39.880 --> 39:43.349
Deran: Yeah?
Yeah, I'm Detective
Louise Thompson.

39:43.351 --> 39:44.951
Riverside County
Cold Case.

39:44.953 --> 39:48.020
So, you're responsible
for all this bullshit?
Bullshit?

39:48.022 --> 39:49.755
David: How long until my client
is finished processing?

39:49.757 --> 39:52.024
Oh, Andrew Cody's gonna
spend the night with us.

39:52.026 --> 39:53.559
On what legal basis?

39:53.561 --> 39:56.963
He confessed to the murder
of Catherine Belen.

39:56.965 --> 39:58.430
No, he didn't.

39:58.432 --> 40:00.533
I want to talk
to my client.

40:01.970 --> 40:03.836
No, he didn't.

40:03.838 --> 40:09.708
♪♪

40:09.710 --> 40:15.313
♪♪

40:15.315 --> 40:18.784
You want a pizza
or something?

40:18.786 --> 40:21.119
Uh...

40:21.121 --> 40:23.089
sure.

40:25.860 --> 40:27.526
Alright.

40:27.528 --> 40:34.800
♪♪

40:34.802 --> 40:37.069
[ Cellphone ringing ]

40:37.071 --> 40:46.879
♪♪

40:46.881 --> 40:56.622
♪♪

40:56.624 --> 40:58.957
That them?

40:58.959 --> 41:02.094
Yeah.

41:02.096 --> 41:04.163
They coming home?

41:06.567 --> 41:09.568
The cops say
Pope confessed.

41:09.570 --> 41:11.837
To the assault?

41:11.839 --> 41:13.639
To the murder.

41:13.641 --> 41:21.047
♪♪

41:21.049 --> 41:23.181
[ Door opens ]

41:23.183 --> 41:28.320
♪♪

41:28.322 --> 41:30.323
Come here, baby.

41:35.195 --> 41:37.263
You feeling better?

41:39.800 --> 41:41.567
Come here. Sit.

41:53.614 --> 41:56.148
♪♪

41:56.150 --> 42:00.086
Anything you want,
I'll get it for you.

42:00.088 --> 42:02.088
You know that, right?

42:02.090 --> 42:11.563
♪♪

42:11.565 --> 42:20.773
♪♪

42:20.775 --> 42:30.048
♪♪

42:30.050 --> 42:31.984
Hey.

42:31.986 --> 42:34.320
Hey.

42:34.322 --> 42:36.655
How's she doing?

42:36.657 --> 42:38.924
She's up.

42:38.926 --> 42:40.526
Pissed
I ruined her high.

42:40.528 --> 42:42.394
Yeah,
sounds about right.

42:42.396 --> 42:44.196
They're, uh,
keeping her overnight.

42:44.198 --> 42:46.632
Something about
potassium levels.

42:48.469 --> 42:50.169
Okay.

42:53.007 --> 42:54.340
What's that?

42:54.342 --> 42:56.475
I have some apartments
near the Strand.

42:56.477 --> 42:58.144
They haven't sold yet.
They're pretty new.

42:58.146 --> 43:00.613
I want you to move
into one.

43:00.615 --> 43:03.249
You're giving me
an apartment?

43:05.886 --> 43:08.420
I'm giving you an out.

43:08.422 --> 43:12.358
'Cause Noah's not gonna change,
and neither is Cindy.

43:12.360 --> 43:14.026
That's a lot
to think about.

43:14.028 --> 43:15.894
No, it's not.

43:15.896 --> 43:22.701
♪♪

43:22.703 --> 43:24.637
Are you okay?

43:24.639 --> 43:27.305
Just this shit
with my family.

43:27.307 --> 43:30.176
Business stuff?

43:30.178 --> 43:33.179
My uncle's being charged
with murder.

43:33.181 --> 43:35.447
Oh, my God.

43:35.449 --> 43:37.550
Are you --
Are you alright?

43:39.988 --> 43:43.189
I don't know.
It could change a lot of things.

43:43.191 --> 43:47.660
What a shitty day.
I'm sorry.

43:47.662 --> 43:52.464
♪♪

43:52.466 --> 43:55.401
Hey.
Got an idea for another job.

43:55.403 --> 43:57.069
I don't wanna do
another job, Tommy.

43:57.071 --> 43:58.270
Well, let me tell you
what it is.

43:58.272 --> 44:00.138
No.
Go home, alright?
What?

44:00.140 --> 44:02.074
Hey, don't touch me!
Go home!

44:02.076 --> 44:03.809
Alright?!
It's over!

44:06.280 --> 44:08.146
You're fired.

44:08.148 --> 44:15.821
♪♪

44:15.823 --> 44:18.224
[ Engine shuts off ]

44:18.226 --> 44:25.364
♪♪

44:25.366 --> 44:32.771
♪♪

44:32.773 --> 44:39.912
♪♪

44:39.914 --> 44:41.647
Hey.

44:42.116 --> 44:44.317
[ Sniffling ]

44:47.455 --> 44:49.922
Can't stay at my place.

44:49.924 --> 44:51.857
[ Sniffles ]

44:51.859 --> 44:54.260
Can I spend
the night here?

44:55.063 --> 44:57.063
Of course.

44:57.065 --> 45:07.005
♪♪

45:07.007 --> 45:16.682
♪♪

45:16.684 --> 45:26.425
♪♪

45:26.427 --> 45:36.235
♪♪

45:36.237 --> 45:46.244
♪                    ♪♪

45:46.246 --> 45:55.922
♪♪

